# Level & Anvil website rules

## Project context
This repository is for the public-facing Level & Anvil website.
It is not the internal operations web app.
Do not treat this project like a large SaaS dashboard unless explicitly requested.

## Primary goals
- Make small, safe, high-value improvements
- Preserve production stability
- Improve clarity, trust, conversion, and polish
- Favor fast load times and simple maintainable code
- Keep the codebase understandable for a small business owner

## Change philosophy
- Prefer minimal, surgical edits over broad rewrites
- Do not redesign architecture unless explicitly asked
- Do not replace working code just because a different pattern is possible
- Avoid unrelated refactors
- Preserve existing routes, page intent, and live business messaging unless asked to change them

## Before making changes
Always:
1. inspect the relevant files first
2. identify the smallest set of files needed
3. explain what will change
4. avoid touching unrelated files

## When proposing work
Prioritize:
1. bug fixes
2. broken UX or layout issues
3. mobile responsiveness
4. conversion improvements
5. SEO improvements
6. code cleanup only when it directly supports the requested task

## Guardrails
- Do not invent backend systems that do not already exist
- Do not add heavy dependencies unless clearly justified
- Do not add authentication, dashboards, admin tools, or database features unless explicitly requested
- Do not create fake integrations or placeholder logic presented as production-ready
- Do not silently change brand voice, service positioning, or business claims
- Do not remove existing content unless it is clearly obsolete or the task requires it

## Output expectations
When completing a task:
- summarize what changed
- list files changed
- note anything that still needs manual review
- mention any assumptions made